We were planning a vacation.

246
00:13:04,280 --> 00:13:07,600
(officer whispering)

247
00:13:08,880 --> 00:13:12,520
When do we get to, uh,
see the body?

248
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:14,520
Lt'll be a couple of days.

249
00:13:14,560 --> 00:13:17,280
But I have to warn you...

250
00:13:17,320 --> 00:13:19,680
he died from a self-inflicted
gunshot wound to the head,

251
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:23,040
so he's pretty unrecognizable.

252
00:13:24,880 --> 00:13:26,760
I'll give you two a moment.

253
00:13:58,040 --> 00:14:00,600
They said he was
unrecognizable, right?

254
00:14:00,640 --> 00:14:02,720
How can they be sure
it's Sammy?

255
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:08,000
It's not him.

256
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:12,880
It's not him.

257
00:14:49,880 --> 00:14:53,200
I can't remember which books
go on which shelves.

258
00:14:54,720 --> 00:14:56,520
I don't know.

259
00:14:58,440 --> 00:15:00,600
He's gonna be so upset.

260
00:15:50,040 --> 00:15:52,920
(crying)

261
00:16:07,680 --> 00:16:09,600
Oh God.

262
00:16:38,280 --> 00:16:41,320
(groaning)

263
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:45,200
(crying)

264
00:16:56,320 --> 00:16:59,240
(phone ringing)

265
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:07,400
Hello?

266
00:17:07,440 --> 00:17:09,320
Speaking.

267
00:17:16,560 --> 00:17:19,160
Sorry, uh, we have no comment.

268
00:17:20,920 --> 00:17:24,080
(phone ringing)

269
00:17:40,360 --> 00:17:43,880
(chatter)

270
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:46,840
(phone continues ringing)

271
00:17:52,480 --> 00:17:55,120
Why aren't you answering that?

272
00:17:55,160 --> 00:17:57,680
There are all these
news vans outside.

273
00:17:57,720 --> 00:17:59,720
What?

274
00:17:59,760 --> 00:18:01,960
They must have released his name.

275
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:05,080
Kate: We just lost our son.
What do they want from us?

276
00:18:05,120 --> 00:18:06,960
Bill:
We're news.

277
00:18:06,960 --> 00:18:09,960
- (phone ringing)
- Ignore it.

278
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:12,480
We should go upstairs.
They'll start peeking in the windows.

279
00:18:12,520 --> 00:18:14,760
Are they just gonna stay
out there all day waiting?

280
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:17,840
Come on. Come on.

281
00:18:57,040 --> 00:18:59,600
Newscaster on TV: Is known
beyond the shooter's identity.

282
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:04,000
Students from his dorm only say
that he was quiet and kept to himself.

283
00:19:04,040 --> 00:19:06,720
We go now to 7 News
reporter Michael Call live

284
00:19:06,760 --> 00:19:08,600
outside the shooter's
childhood home.

285
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:10,160
Bill:
Turn that off.

286
00:19:10,200 --> 00:19:12,360
Someone could see
the light from outside.

287
00:19:13,960 --> 00:19:16,360
They'll just start
ringing the bell again

288
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:19,760
if they find out we're home.

289
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:33,680
Kate:
Are they still there?

290
00:19:33,720 --> 00:19:36,360
The last one's finally leaving.

291
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:38,800
But they'll probably
be back in the morning.

292
00:19:44,160 --> 00:19:47,280
- I'm so sorry.
- Thanks.

293
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:06,320
- You redid the kitchen, huh?
- Yeah, a couple months ago.

294
00:20:06,360 --> 00:20:08,400
- Bill: It's nice.
- You don't have to wait on us really.

295
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:09,840
It's nothing.

296
00:20:09,880 --> 00:20:11,600
Woman: I've put some
fresh towels in the bathroom.

297
00:20:11,640 --> 00:20:13,080
Thanks.

298
00:20:13,120 --> 00:20:15,080
This looks good.

299
00:20:15,120 --> 00:20:16,840
- Is Dylan asleep?
- Yeah.

300
00:20:16,880 --> 00:20:18,520
You'll see him tomorrow.

301
00:20:19,520 --> 00:20:22,880
Delicious.
What'd you marinate this in?

302
00:20:22,920 --> 00:20:26,080
Oh, it's just some bottled stuff
I got at the supermarket.

303
00:20:26,120 --> 00:20:29,440
(sniffles)

304
00:20:29,480 --> 00:20:31,320
(sighs)

305
00:20:31,360 --> 00:20:33,840
I'm sorry.

306
00:20:33,880 --> 00:20:35,200
I just can't believe it.

307
00:20:38,840 --> 00:20:40,360
Was he okay?

308
00:20:40,400 --> 00:20:42,400
I mean before, you know?

309
00:20:42,440 --> 00:20:44,360
Bill:
We thought so.

310
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:46,800
We... we didn't see him much.

311
00:20:46,840 --> 00:20:49,480
The first year of college
is always hard.

312
00:20:49,520 --> 00:20:52,480
Being away from home
alone, I guess.

313
00:20:52,520 --> 00:20:54,880
- Yeah, of course.
- Woman: Was he depressed?

314
00:20:54,960 --> 00:20:56,800
Was he doing drugs?

315
00:20:56,840 --> 00:21:01,320
- Trish.
- I'm sorry. Sorry.

316
00:21:01,360 --> 00:21:03,840
Hey, did I tell you that Mom
bought a new car?

317
00:21:03,880 --> 00:21:05,280
What kind?

318
00:21:05,360 --> 00:21:10,080
He was a little quieter
than usual, that's all.

319
00:21:23,600 --> 00:21:26,240
Which side do you want?

320
00:21:26,280 --> 00:21:28,640
Uh, it doesn't matter.
You pick.

321
00:21:34,240 --> 00:21:36,560
Your brother's doing
a nice job on the house.

322
00:21:38,160 --> 00:21:40,880
This is probably worth twice
what they paid by now.

323
00:21:40,920 --> 00:21:45,160
Did you call work and tell them
you won't be in for a while?

324
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:46,600
No.

325
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:49,760
They're gonna be staked out
at your office too.

326
00:22:01,640 --> 00:22:05,160
(distant dog barking)

327
00:22:12,680 --> 00:22:14,880
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

328
00:22:18,080 --> 00:22:19,720
And uh...
(clears throat)

329
00:22:19,760 --> 00:22:21,800
Thanks, I mean for...

330
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:24,280
Oh no. Hey, come on,
you're family.

331
00:22:24,320 --> 00:22:28,080
If you need anything,
you know, just ask.

332
00:22:31,280 --> 00:22:33,160
Morning.
(clears throat)

333
00:22:33,200 --> 00:22:35,840
There she is.
How'd you sleep?

334
00:22:35,880 --> 00:22:38,160
Uh, well, thank you.

335
00:22:41,520 --> 00:22:45,000
Good morning there, Dylan.
How you doing?

336
00:22:45,040 --> 00:22:47,040
Man: Trish taught him to read
the nutritional labels.

337
00:22:47,080 --> 00:22:48,360
Trish:
And that backfired.

338
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:51,920
Now all he wants to eat are the ones
with 13g of sugar per serving.

339
00:22:51,960 --> 00:22:53,840
Oh my goodness.
And you let him, huh?

340
00:22:53,840 --> 00:22:56,000
Not always.

341
00:23:00,040 --> 00:23:01,800
Can I make you any breakfast?

342
00:23:01,840 --> 00:23:04,040
Oh no, thank you.
Just some coffee please.

343
00:23:04,080 --> 00:23:06,160
I got it. I got it.

344
00:23:07,520 --> 00:23:10,400
- That looks good.
- Yeah.

345
00:23:11,720 --> 00:23:14,440
Here you go.

346
00:23:14,480 --> 00:23:16,480
Come on, buddy.
You're done.

347
00:23:18,960 --> 00:23:20,960
Only 15 minutes.
Then we get ready for school.

348
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:25,160
- (TV turns on)
- Mommy, Sammy's on TV!

349
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:28,920
This was completely
in your power to avoid today.

350
00:23:31,720 --> 00:23:33,280
Except you only leave me
one option.

351
00:23:33,320 --> 00:23:35,560
Oh my God.

352
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:37,560
And now you all have blood
on your hands.

353
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:40,360
You vandalized my heart.

354
00:23:40,400 --> 00:23:41,960
Come on, sweetie.
Let's get ready for school.

355
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:43,920
- Dylan: But it's not 15 minutes yet.
- Man: Shh.

356
00:23:43,960 --> 00:23:45,480
Sam:
Maybe now you'll listen to me.

357
00:24:01,800 --> 00:24:04,040
- Okay, mister, time for bed.
- But I'm not done.

358
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:06,560
- Yes, you are.
- No!

359
00:24:06,600 --> 00:24:09,080
- Trish: Dylan, let's go. Come on.
- Buddy.

360
00:24:09,120 --> 00:24:10,720
He is stubborn.

361
00:24:10,760 --> 00:24:13,320
Sammy was like that too
at his age.

362
00:24:14,880 --> 00:24:17,760
We need to issue a statement.

363
00:24:17,800 --> 00:24:19,720
What for?

364
00:24:19,760 --> 00:24:21,840
It's the right thing to do.

365
00:24:21,880 --> 00:24:25,600
You know, l... I just
mean something simple

366
00:24:25,640 --> 00:24:29,200
just expressing our remorse
and sadness.

367
00:24:29,240 --> 00:24:30,680
Kate:
Remorse?

368
00:24:30,720 --> 00:24:32,760
If we don't give the victims'
families something,

369
00:24:32,800 --> 00:24:36,360
they're gonna think we... we don't
feel bad about what Sammy did.

370
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:42,800
Kate?

371
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:49,800
(water running)

372
00:24:49,840 --> 00:24:51,880
- Hey.
- Hey.

373
00:24:51,920 --> 00:24:53,960
Do you use bleach in your whites?

374
00:24:54,000 --> 00:24:55,760
Uh yeah, I think.

375
00:24:57,680 --> 00:25:01,360
Katie, you know that he didn't mean
that you don't feel bad.

376
00:25:01,400 --> 00:25:03,680
It's just that
you can't wait too long.

377
00:25:03,720 --> 00:25:05,480
- I know.
- People aren't thinking straight

378
00:25:05,520 --> 00:25:07,880
and you gotta give them something
so they know that you're on their side.

379
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:10,000
Eric, I know.

380
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:13,680
Okay.

381
00:25:38,960 --> 00:25:41,440
(sighs)

382
00:25:55,160 --> 00:25:57,400
We are deeply sorry
for the devastation

383
00:25:57,440 --> 00:26:00,120
our son has caused.

384
00:26:00,160 --> 00:26:02,160
Like all the victims' parents,

385
00:26:02,200 --> 00:26:05,480
we are shocked
and utterly heartbroken.

386
00:26:05,520 --> 00:26:07,600
Please allow us our privacy

387
00:26:07,640 --> 00:26:10,320
as we mourn the loss
of our own son

388
00:26:10,360 --> 00:26:12,680
and try to find
the strength to move on

389
00:26:12,720 --> 00:26:15,600
from this horrible,
inexplicable tragedy.

390
00:26:17,960 --> 00:26:19,520
Do you mind if I go?

391
00:26:21,040 --> 00:26:22,680
Sure.

392
00:27:31,640 --> 00:27:33,240
That's okay, I've got it.

393
00:27:36,320 --> 00:27:38,240
(sighs)

394
00:27:39,880 --> 00:27:42,240
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

395
00:27:56,880 --> 00:27:59,080
Thinking about taking a walk.

396
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:05,360
(distant children playing)

397
00:28:05,400 --> 00:28:08,040
Kate: It's good to be
out of the house.

398
00:28:08,080 --> 00:28:09,720
Bill: Yeah, Trish and your brother
are being great,

399
00:28:09,760 --> 00:28:14,640
but after a while,
I just want them to...

400
00:28:14,680 --> 00:28:18,000
I don't know... ignore me.

401
00:28:18,040 --> 00:28:20,560
Kate: Mm.
(inhales)

402
00:28:20,600 --> 00:28:23,280
Mm, do you smell the jasmine?
(sniffs)

403
00:28:23,320 --> 00:28:27,720
- Smell it?
- (sniffs) No.

404
00:28:27,760 --> 00:28:32,360
It's that sweet, flowery thing.
You don't smell that?

405
00:28:32,400 --> 00:28:36,000
(chuckles)
I thought that was you...

406
00:28:36,040 --> 00:28:39,320
your shampoo or your lotion
or something.

407
00:28:39,360 --> 00:28:41,040
Kate:
Nah.

408
00:29:07,480 --> 00:29:08,600
(door closes)

409
00:29:08,640 --> 00:29:11,360
Bill: Trish gave us some Ambien
in case we need it.

410
00:29:15,880 --> 00:29:18,040
Did we do something?

411
00:29:19,320 --> 00:29:21,320
L... I mean, how could he do it?
Did we do something?

412
00:29:21,360 --> 00:29:23,800
- Did we not do something?
- No.

413
00:29:25,200 --> 00:29:28,200
No. We gave him everything
he could want.

414
00:29:28,240 --> 00:29:30,080
But he was...
he was such a quiet kid.

415
00:29:30,120 --> 00:29:31,160
He was lonely.

416
00:29:31,200 --> 00:29:32,840
He never played with
the neighbor kids.

417
00:29:32,880 --> 00:29:33,920
We should have
known that there...

418
00:29:33,960 --> 00:29:36,360
Why does it have to be
our fault? Huh?

419
00:29:36,400 --> 00:29:38,200
We did the best we could.

420
00:29:40,080 --> 00:29:41,800
- Come on, let's go to sleep.
- I don't want to go to sleep.

421
00:29:41,840 --> 00:29:44,400
- I want to talk about this.
- What is there to talk about?

422
00:29:46,440 --> 00:29:51,880
You were a terrific mother.
We... we didn't do anything wrong.

423
00:29:51,920 --> 00:29:54,360
Okay?

424
00:29:54,400 --> 00:29:55,720
Well, I'm tired.
I'm going to bed.

425
00:29:55,760 --> 00:29:58,360
Okay, goodnight.

426
00:30:01,560 --> 00:30:03,520
I was thinking maybe
I'd go back to work tomorrow.

427
00:30:03,560 --> 00:30:05,440
Okay.

428
00:30:07,160 --> 00:30:10,320
I might swing by the house,
get some mail,

429
00:30:10,360 --> 00:30:12,280
make sure everything's okay.

430
00:30:13,520 --> 00:30:16,360
Bonnie said the reporters
are still there.

431
00:30:19,640 --> 00:30:22,120
Fine, I won't go.

432
00:30:22,160 --> 00:30:24,200
I didn't say that.
You can do whatever you want.

433
00:30:34,800 --> 00:30:37,840
You're not gonna be able to live there
after all this, you know.

434
00:30:39,760 --> 00:30:42,440
Maybe we should start
talking to realtors.

435
00:30:47,280 --> 00:30:49,160
(sizzling)

436
00:30:52,280 --> 00:30:54,480
- Morning, Trish.
- Morning.

437
00:30:54,520 --> 00:30:56,800
- Can I help?
- Oh no, I'm good.

438
00:30:56,840 --> 00:30:58,280
Do you want me to get
Dylan up for school?

439
00:30:58,320 --> 00:31:00,200
- Oh, he's up.
- Oh.

440
00:31:00,240 --> 00:31:01,640
Maybe I can help him
get dressed then.

441
00:31:01,680 --> 00:31:04,080
Eric's doing that right now.

442
00:31:04,080 --> 00:31:07,560
- Please let me do something.
- Oh.

443
00:31:07,600 --> 00:31:10,520
- You can make Dylan's lunch.
- Great.

444
00:31:13,520 --> 00:31:16,480
Hey, did you ever notice
your fridge doors were uneven?

445
00:31:16,520 --> 00:31:19,240
See, this one's a little lower
than the other.

446
00:31:19,280 --> 00:31:21,320
I'll have Eric take a look at that.

447
00:31:26,400 --> 00:31:28,680
- Bill: Hey, Harry. It's Bill.
- Harry over phone: Bill!

448
00:31:28,720 --> 00:31:31,480
Jesus, buddy, how are you doing?
How's Kate?

449
00:31:31,520 --> 00:31:33,960
Fine. Uh, fine.

450
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:35,680
She's tough.

451
00:31:35,720 --> 00:31:37,960
So l... I was thinking
things must be piling up

452
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:40,920
- pretty high there without me, huh?
- Don't even worry about it.

453
00:31:40,960 --> 00:31:44,360
I talked to HR and got you
four weeks of paid leave.

454
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:46,000
I figured you could use the time.

455
00:31:46,040 --> 00:31:50,440
Oh well, you know,
I don't mind coming in,

456
00:31:50,480 --> 00:31:53,480
making sure, you know,
nothing's falling through the cracks.

457
00:31:53,520 --> 00:31:57,320
Don't you worry about us, Billy boy.
You just take care of yourself.

458
00:31:57,360 --> 00:32:01,120
And if there's anything
I can do, you let me know.

459
00:32:01,160 --> 00:32:03,120
Uh sure, okay.

460
00:32:03,160 --> 00:32:05,080
Thanks. Bye.

461
00:32:19,080 --> 00:32:20,960
I thought you were
going to work today.

462
00:32:21,040 --> 00:32:22,960
Nope.

463
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:25,160
Good. You can go
to the cemetery with me.

464
00:32:25,200 --> 00:32:27,560
Yeah, I'm just gonna
go out for a bit first.

465
00:33:00,080 --> 00:33:02,200
You can stop right up here.

466
00:33:03,320 --> 00:33:05,240
This is good.

467
00:33:07,440 --> 00:33:09,480
Thank you.
Keep the change.

468
00:33:20,720 --> 00:33:23,760
Eric: I want you to eat
just a little bit more, buddy.

469
00:33:23,800 --> 00:33:25,720
Nice!

470
00:33:27,120 --> 00:33:29,040
Eric:
Billy, is that you?

471
00:33:31,400 --> 00:33:33,680
- Trish: You got a workout in.
- Sit down, man.

472
00:33:33,720 --> 00:33:35,920
Your wife made a feast.

473
00:33:35,960 --> 00:33:37,920
Kate: Maybe you should
take a shower first.

474
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:40,120
Yeah, I think I will.

475
00:33:40,160 --> 00:33:41,720
Kate:
Oh, sit sit. I got it.

476
00:33:41,760 --> 00:33:43,680
Dylan, would you like
some pie and ice cream, sir?

477
00:33:43,720 --> 00:33:45,600
- Yes, please.
- I want you to eat one more.

478
00:33:45,640 --> 00:33:47,240
One more, one more
before you get ice cream.

479
00:33:47,280 --> 00:33:48,760
Okay.

480
00:34:03,560 --> 00:34:05,840
- 'Night.
- 'Night.

481
00:34:16,560 --> 00:34:18,280
(sighs)

482
00:34:18,320 --> 00:34:19,440
Woman on TV:
...in your bathroom.

483
00:34:19,480 --> 00:34:21,080
It cuts through
the nasty ring around the...

484
00:34:21,120 --> 00:34:22,560
- (channel changes)
- (laughter)

485
00:34:22,640 --> 00:34:24,280
- (channel changes)
- And I know some of you

486
00:34:24,320 --> 00:34:27,960
are back home thinking,
"Well, the parents are victims too."

487
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:30,920
No, they're not.
They raised this kid.

488
00:34:30,960 --> 00:34:33,920
And I don't care
if he's a legal adult or not.

489
00:34:33,960 --> 00:34:37,280
It's the parents who are
ultimately responsible.

490
00:34:37,320 --> 00:34:40,040
And we should find them,
whatever rock they're hiding under,

491
00:34:40,080 --> 00:34:43,360
so the grieving parents
can take a crack at 'em.

492
00:34:43,400 --> 00:34:45,280
But here's the real question, folks:

493
00:34:45,360 --> 00:34:47,360
Do they have any other kids
running around

494
00:34:47,400 --> 00:34:49,160
that I need to worry about?

495
00:34:49,200 --> 00:34:52,240
Because after their track record
with this little bugger,

496
00:34:52,280 --> 00:34:54,120
I don't really want to meet
the rest of the family.

497
00:34:54,160 --> 00:34:56,720
And I sure as hell
don't want the little psycho

498
00:34:56,760 --> 00:35:00,240
going to school
