And onions, that's right.

751
00:53:04,080 --> 00:53:06,920
Well, you know what?
You can have those.

752
00:53:06,960 --> 00:53:11,200
I'm gonna go for the Lance
Fresh Toastchee crackers.

753
00:53:11,240 --> 00:53:13,480
Not "cheese," "chee."

754
00:53:13,520 --> 00:53:14,640
- (bag pops)
- Whoa!

755
00:53:14,680 --> 00:53:17,040
Ooh, wrong end.

756
00:53:17,080 --> 00:53:18,520
Mmm.

757
00:53:18,560 --> 00:53:21,400
- Mmm.
- Not bad.

758
00:53:21,440 --> 00:53:23,640
(laughing)

759
00:53:23,680 --> 00:53:26,280
Mm, it's a little dry.

760
00:53:30,600 --> 00:53:34,400
- You're so weird.
- Mm-hmm.

761
00:53:37,720 --> 00:53:39,560
More.

762
00:53:40,760 --> 00:53:42,200
Thank you.

763
00:53:44,280 --> 00:53:47,280
- Bon apptit.
- Mm.

764
00:53:55,600 --> 00:53:59,200
I don't know why I never
let Sammy eat junk food.

765
00:53:59,240 --> 00:54:02,600
- It's really quite nutritious.
- Plus it's darned tasty.

766
00:54:02,640 --> 00:54:05,280
Mm-hmm.
Cheers to that.

767
00:54:06,760 --> 00:54:07,760
Ah!

768
00:54:07,800 --> 00:54:11,080
Oh, and you know the best part?

769
00:54:11,120 --> 00:54:13,600
- Hmm?
- (laughing)

770
00:54:13,680 --> 00:54:15,760
No dishes to rinse.

771
00:54:15,800 --> 00:54:18,600
No, but all the crumbs in the bed.

772
00:54:18,640 --> 00:54:21,880
Oh God!
No crumbs in the bed!

773
00:54:21,920 --> 00:54:24,280
- Stop it. Stop it.
- No crumbs in the bed.

774
00:54:24,320 --> 00:54:26,280
Oh, that's so gross.

775
00:54:28,840 --> 00:54:31,880
- (laughing)
- What time is it?

776
00:54:34,240 --> 00:54:37,160
- Who cares?
- So what do you wanna do now?

777
00:54:38,920 --> 00:54:42,160
- Let's play cards.
- I thought you said one was missing.

778
00:54:44,360 --> 00:54:47,360
Five-card draw.
Nothing's wild.

779
00:54:47,400 --> 00:54:49,000
Right. And what are we betting?

780
00:54:51,760 --> 00:54:53,680
What are we, 16 again?

781
00:54:54,760 --> 00:54:56,440
- (grunts)
- I fold.

782
00:54:57,520 --> 00:54:59,120
Oh.

783
00:55:01,840 --> 00:55:04,040
(giggles)

784
00:55:04,080 --> 00:55:08,520
- You're stuck.
- Help! My head.

785
00:56:34,000 --> 00:56:36,840
(indistinct conversation)

786
00:56:49,520 --> 00:56:51,920
(Kate laughs)

787
00:56:56,840 --> 00:56:59,400
Kate's voice:
What day is today?

788
00:56:59,440 --> 00:57:01,680
Bill's voice:
I have no idea.

789
00:57:05,360 --> 00:57:08,240
You know we can't go on
like this forever.

790
00:57:10,720 --> 00:57:12,360
I know.

791
00:57:15,000 --> 00:57:17,400
But we can do it for a little longer.

792
00:57:17,440 --> 00:57:19,160
Yeah.

793
00:57:30,560 --> 00:57:33,920
You want me to come with you?

794
00:57:33,960 --> 00:57:36,800
I'm just gonna make sure
everything's okay,

795
00:57:36,880 --> 00:57:39,240
grab some clothes and come back.

796
00:57:39,240 --> 00:57:41,960
- The bills can wait, you know.
- I'll be quick.

797
00:57:42,000 --> 00:57:45,440
I'll let Bonnie know, so she doesn't
accidentally call the cops on you.

798
00:57:54,760 --> 00:57:56,160
Bye.

799
00:58:40,520 --> 00:58:42,480
Yeah.

800
00:59:07,240 --> 00:59:08,920
(loud thumps)

801
00:59:12,200 --> 00:59:14,000
(objects clatter)

802
00:59:22,280 --> 00:59:24,160
(clattering continues)

803
00:59:42,080 --> 00:59:44,000
(rustling, clattering)

804
00:59:52,360 --> 00:59:56,200
Dude, he's got an award
for perfect attendance.

805
00:59:56,240 --> 00:59:58,920
(laughs)
Yeah.

806
00:59:58,960 --> 01:00:00,200
Nice.

807
01:00:00,240 --> 01:00:02,640
What are you doing in here?

808
01:00:04,160 --> 01:00:05,880
Uh...

809
01:00:07,080 --> 01:00:09,720
What are you doing
in my son's room?

810
01:00:09,760 --> 01:00:13,400
I'm sorry. L...
I didn't know you'd be here.

811
01:00:13,440 --> 01:00:16,320
What are you doing
in my son's room?!

812
01:00:16,360 --> 01:00:18,360
I can't breathe.

813
01:00:20,080 --> 01:00:22,000
- You fucking psycho!
- (glass breaks)

814
01:00:22,040 --> 01:00:23,960
Ah!

815
01:00:28,560 --> 01:00:30,560
Kate:
Bill?

816
01:00:30,600 --> 01:00:32,240
Yeah. I'm back.

817
01:00:37,360 --> 01:00:41,080
- Did you see Bonnie?
- No.

818
01:00:47,760 --> 01:00:49,320
I feel overdressed.

819
01:00:51,400 --> 01:00:53,720
Good. Look at you.
You changed your shirt.

820
01:00:53,760 --> 01:00:55,680
The other one
was getting a little ripe.

821
01:00:55,720 --> 01:00:56,920
Yeah.

822
01:00:58,920 --> 01:01:00,600
- What happened to your hand?
- Oh, nothing.

823
01:01:00,640 --> 01:01:03,080
I just... I cut it
on a piece of glass.

824
01:01:03,120 --> 01:01:05,520
- It's fine.
- Are you sure? It looks bad.

825
01:01:05,560 --> 01:01:07,000
Yeah, it's fine.
It's fine.

826
01:01:10,200 --> 01:01:12,520
Oh good, you got me
some new clothes.

827
01:01:12,560 --> 01:01:14,920
I'm sick of wearing the same thing.

828
01:01:16,320 --> 01:01:18,200
Junk mail.

829
01:01:18,240 --> 01:01:20,520
And what is this?

830
01:01:20,560 --> 01:01:22,520
Would someone be looking
for a rematch?

831
01:01:26,640 --> 01:01:28,480
What?

832
01:01:30,760 --> 01:01:33,320
- Is everything okay?
- Yeah yeah.

833
01:01:34,440 --> 01:01:36,680
I'm just tired, you know?

834
01:01:40,720 --> 01:01:42,600
Yeah.

835
01:01:57,800 --> 01:01:59,960
(DVD tray clicks)

836
01:02:03,920 --> 01:02:05,840
Oh my God, Bill.

837
01:02:10,120 --> 01:02:12,040
- Mom and Dad...
- Oh my God.

838
01:02:12,080 --> 01:02:14,000
Oh my God.

839
01:02:17,320 --> 01:02:19,480
...l'm sorry.

840
01:02:24,600 --> 01:02:26,400
Please don't hate me.

841
01:02:31,600 --> 01:02:33,400
Kate: Oh.

842
01:02:34,600 --> 01:02:36,440
Bill: No, I don't... I don't
want to see it again.

843
01:02:36,480 --> 01:02:39,720
No, but... but it's Sammy.
It's our Sammy.

844
01:02:39,760 --> 01:02:44,240
- No, it's not. It's not him.
- Of course it is.

845
01:02:44,280 --> 01:02:46,120
That's the real him,

846
01:02:46,120 --> 01:02:48,680
not what those awful
television stations keep playing.

847
01:02:48,720 --> 01:02:50,640
- This is him.
- No, it's not. It's not.

848
01:02:51,960 --> 01:02:55,840
Well, it was him
until they changed him.

849
01:02:55,880 --> 01:02:58,680
- They made him into that.
- No no no. It happened...

850
01:02:59,720 --> 01:03:02,640
it happened way before
he got to college.

851
01:03:02,680 --> 01:03:07,400
And l... I don't know how,
but we did it.

852
01:03:08,600 --> 01:03:10,520
We messed him up.
We, uh...

853
01:03:12,040 --> 01:03:14,440
maybe we didn't
give him any hope

854
01:03:14,440 --> 01:03:17,840
or, you know, we didn't exactly
show him how to be happy.

855
01:03:17,880 --> 01:03:19,720
- How can you say that?
- He wasn't well.

856
01:03:19,720 --> 01:03:23,040
He was depressed and...
and irrational

857
01:03:23,080 --> 01:03:26,160
and angry.

858
01:03:27,880 --> 01:03:30,480
Well, everyone gets
depressed and angry,

859
01:03:30,520 --> 01:03:32,360
but that's still no explanation.

860
01:03:32,360 --> 01:03:34,840
We don't know why
he did what he did.

861
01:03:36,280 --> 01:03:40,320
And I seem to be the only one
that cares about asking why.

862
01:03:40,360 --> 01:03:43,200
You keep asking why because...

863
01:03:44,560 --> 01:03:46,200
because you're looking
for someone to tell us

864
01:03:46,240 --> 01:03:48,840
that we're not responsible.

865
01:03:48,880 --> 01:03:51,840
And you keep avoiding it because
you assume we are responsible.

866
01:03:51,880 --> 01:03:53,960
Because he... he did it, Kate.
He did it.

867
01:03:54,000 --> 01:03:56,360
He walked into
those classrooms and...

868
01:03:56,400 --> 01:03:58,360
and he actually shot
all those people...

869
01:03:58,400 --> 01:04:00,320
- his teachers, his friends!
- No, I'm not listening to this.

870
01:04:00,360 --> 01:04:02,000
- All right? He's a murderer!
- Shut up!

871
01:04:02,040 --> 01:04:05,080
- He's a murderer and it's our fault!
- Shut up!

872
01:04:05,120 --> 01:04:07,400
You should be defending him.
You're his father.

873
01:04:07,400 --> 01:04:09,160
Well, there is no defense
for what he did!

874
01:04:09,160 --> 01:04:11,720
(sobbing)
I don't want to hear this anymore.

875
01:04:11,720 --> 01:04:13,720
I don't even know who you are!

876
01:04:13,760 --> 01:04:15,200
That's right,
you don't know who I am.

877
01:04:15,280 --> 01:04:17,480
You never did.
You never even tried to.

878
01:04:17,520 --> 01:04:20,200
You don't know me and you sure as hell
didn't know your own son!

879
01:04:20,240 --> 01:04:22,120
Do you want to know
whose fault it is?

880
01:04:22,120 --> 01:04:23,880
It's your fault!

881
01:04:23,920 --> 01:04:26,400
If you weren't such
an emotionally absent

882
01:04:26,440 --> 01:04:29,120
clich of a father,
this wouldn't have happened.

883
01:04:29,160 --> 01:04:31,520
- He... he would be happy.
- So what, you're putting it all on me?

884
01:04:31,560 --> 01:04:34,160
He wasn't happy
because you picked at every...

885
01:04:34,200 --> 01:04:36,120
at every flaw he had,
every mistake.

886
01:04:36,160 --> 01:04:37,800
No no.
At least he knew I cared.

887
01:04:37,800 --> 01:04:42,280
- You and your red pen!
- I was there every time he was sick.

888
01:04:42,320 --> 01:04:45,440
I was the one worried when he didn't
come home for dinner on time.

889
01:04:45,480 --> 01:04:47,080
- And I didn't worry. I didn't worry.
- No! No!

890
01:04:47,080 --> 01:04:49,000
I was the one who checked
his homework.

891
01:04:49,000 --> 01:04:50,800
I was the one who planned
the birthday parties.

892
01:04:50,840 --> 01:04:53,000
I was the one who picked
all of the Christmas gifts.

893
01:04:53,000 --> 01:04:53,960
You... you picked at him.

894
01:04:54,000 --> 01:04:57,560
You picked and picked until he...
till he exploded!

895
01:04:57,600 --> 01:05:01,000
(sobbing)
L... I did the best I could,

896
01:05:01,040 --> 01:05:02,560
but I was by myself.

897
01:05:02,600 --> 01:05:04,480
And where were you?
You were at work.

898
01:05:04,520 --> 01:05:06,920
You were at work.
You put a roof over his head.

899
01:05:06,920 --> 01:05:09,640
But what... where were you?

900
01:05:09,640 --> 01:05:11,880
Where were you?

901
01:05:11,880 --> 01:05:13,800
Yeah.

902
01:05:18,880 --> 01:05:20,440
Go ahead.
Go ahead, leave.

903
01:05:20,480 --> 01:05:22,360
You've been wanting to
for the last 10 years anyway.

904
01:05:22,400 --> 01:05:26,280
Yeah, because I couldn't bear
to be with you!

905
01:05:26,320 --> 01:05:30,560
I wanted to be anywhere else,
but I was... I was stuck.

906
01:05:30,600 --> 01:05:33,200
No, you weren't.
You were not.

907
01:05:33,240 --> 01:05:35,200
You're a big boy.
You could've left anytime.

908
01:05:35,240 --> 01:05:37,920
I was stuck because of Sam!

909
01:05:37,960 --> 01:05:40,600
I stayed because of...
because of him.

910
01:05:40,640 --> 01:05:42,840
And look what...
look what he turned into! Huh?

911
01:05:42,880 --> 01:05:43,960
- Look! Look!
- No! No!

912
01:05:44,000 --> 01:05:46,400
I wish to God we hadn't had him!

913
01:05:46,440 --> 01:05:50,880
- I wish we hadn't fucking had him!
- Don't say it.

914
01:05:52,080 --> 01:05:55,240
Don't say it, please.

915
01:05:55,240 --> 01:05:59,040
- I wish we hadn't had him.
- Oh my... (sobbing)

916
01:05:59,080 --> 01:06:01,000
(crying)

917
01:06:34,640 --> 01:06:37,080
Maybe that's the reason why.

918
01:08:41,400 --> 01:08:43,920
- (ball thuds)
- Kate's voice: Whoa! Nice kick.

919
01:08:43,960 --> 01:08:46,680
(young Sam giggling)

920
01:08:59,600 --> 01:09:02,400
Bill:
Harry. Hey, it's Bill.

921
01:09:02,440 --> 01:09:06,000
- Billy. How are you doing?
- Good.

922
01:09:06,040 --> 01:09:09,040
Look, I was wondering
if you wanted to get a drink.

923
01:09:09,080 --> 01:09:13,680
- Harry: Uh, sure.
- How about today?

924
01:09:14,840 --> 01:09:18,200
Hey, Billy, sorry I'm late.
Traffic was terrible.

925
01:09:18,240 --> 01:09:20,840
Have a seat.
Let me get you a cold one.

926
01:09:20,840 --> 01:09:22,760
I can't stay long, but...

927
01:09:25,400 --> 01:09:28,520
- So how are you doing?
- Great.

928
01:09:28,560 --> 01:09:31,520
- And Kate?
- Great...

929
01:09:31,560 --> 01:09:35,040
you know, considering.

930
01:09:35,080 --> 01:09:37,440
- Here you are, sweetie.
- Thank you.

931
01:09:37,480 --> 01:09:40,920
To be honest,
we're not together anymore.

932
01:09:40,960 --> 01:09:43,520
- You're kidding.
- I'm getting my own place.

933
01:09:43,560 --> 01:09:47,360
Don't you think you should just sleep
on a friend's couch for a while?

934
01:09:47,400 --> 01:09:50,160
Try to straighten things out?

935
01:09:50,200 --> 01:09:53,000
I don't have any friends.

936
01:09:53,000 --> 01:09:57,360
Well, I sure hope
you two work it out.

937
01:10:00,120 --> 01:10:02,160
So what can I do for you?

938
01:10:03,560 --> 01:10:05,840
I'm ready to go back to work.

939
01:10:05,880 --> 01:10:08,360
- Are you sure?
- Absolutely.

940
01:10:09,640 --> 01:10:11,080
What did you do to your wrist?

941
01:10:11,120 --> 01:10:13,000
Oh uh, it's nothing.

942
01:10:13,000 --> 01:10:16,040
So what do you...
what do you think?

943
01:10:16,080 --> 01:10:18,440
- Bill...
- I need to do something.

944
01:10:18,440 --> 01:10:20,440
I'm going crazy.

945
01:10:21,800 --> 01:10:24,160
Harry, please.

946
01:10:24,200 --> 01:10:26,200
Look, I gotta get going.

947
01:10:31,240 --> 01:10:33,560
All right, come in next week.

948
01:10:34,760 --> 01:10:36,680
I'll see you Monday?

949
01:10:38,120 --> 01:10:39,840
Thanks.

950
01:10:39,880 --> 01:10:41,760
(footsteps retreating)

951
01:10:45,640 --> 01:10:47,560
(music playing over PA)

952
01:10:53,960 --> 01:10:55,680
Excuse me.

953
01:10:56,840 --> 01:10:58,520
Excuse me.

954
01:10:58,560 --> 01:11:00,240
Thank you.

955
01:11:08,040 --> 01:11:10,080
Kate?

956
01:11:10,120 --> 01:11:12,040
I thought that was you.

957
01:11:12,040 --> 01:11:14,160
Hi. What are you doing here?

958
01:11:14,200 --> 01:11:16,800
I was jonesing
for some Coco Pandas.

959
01:11:16,840 --> 01:11:19,560
Goes with your
quadruple espresso, I guess.

960
01:11:19,560 --> 01:11:21,880
Absolutely.
The sugar-caffeine diet.

961
01:11:21,920 --> 01:11:24,320
Um, can I buy you a cup?

962
01:11:24,360 --> 01:11:27,360
It's... it's not afternoon yet.

963
01:11:46,080 --> 01:11:47,560
Let me give you a hand there.

964
01:11:47,600 --> 01:11:49,480
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

965
01:11:58,280 --> 01:12:01,240
Should I talk about it?
Should I avoid it completely?

966
01:12:01,280 --> 01:12:04,920
Pretend it didn't happen?
I just... no one knew how to act.

967
01:12:05,960 --> 01:12:07,480
Jeez, even your family?

968
01:12:07,520 --> 01:12:10,760
L... I don't know,
I bet all that tiptoeing around

969
01:12:10,760 --> 01:12:12,560
- would get to you after a while.
- No, it's not their fault.

970
01:12:12,600 --> 01:12:14,600
I can't say I'd react
any differently if I was them.

971
01:12:14,640 --> 01:12:17,440
- Can you hand me those, please?
- Was I a total idiot that time?

972
01:12:17,480 --> 01:12:20,000
- Just like a complete, moronic...
- No.

973
01:12:20,040 --> 01:12:22,360
- (laughs) I was.
- Yeah, a little bit.

974
01:12:22,400 --> 01:12:24,440
But you were really sweet.
Thanks for that.

975
01:12:27,080 --> 01:12:30,600
- You want to stay for dinner?
- Um...

976
01:12:31,760 --> 01:12:33,280
Nothing fancy, but...

977
01:12:34,600 --> 01:12:37,000
- Sure, I'd like that.
- Okay.

978
01:12:38,120 --> 01:12:41,720
We haven't had a real dinner
in this house

979
01:12:41,760 --> 01:12:43,200
where we actually
sat down and ate

980
01:12:43,240 --> 01:12:45,960
since Sammy was like
a sophomore in high school, so...

981
01:12:45,960 --> 01:12:47,560
Well, I'm happy
to bring back the tradition.

982
01:12:47,600 --> 01:12:49,000
And it's really good.

983
01:12:49,000 --> 01:12:50,280
I'm not sure I've ever had
mac and cheese

984
01:12:50,280 --> 01:12:52,920
that didn't come out
of a little blue box.

985
01:12:52,960 --> 01:12:55,040
It was his favorite.

986
01:13:00,400 --> 01:13:02,880
Did he have a lot of friends?

987
01:13:02,920 --> 01:13:05,800
Mm, mm-mm.

988
01:13:05,840 --> 01:13:08,680
Now and again,
but he was a really shy kid.

989
01:13:08,680 --> 01:13:10,680
Yeah.

990
01:13:11,880 --> 01:13:14,760
Every year we'd go
to this annual Christmas party...

991
01:13:17,000 --> 01:13:18,400
at Dr. Ko's house.

992
01:13:18,440 --> 01:13:19,440
He was a friend of mine.

993
01:13:19,480 --> 01:13:22,960
And he had this tradition where
before the kids got their gifts,

994
01:13:23,000 --> 01:13:25,160
they had to sing a song
in front of everyone.

995
01:13:25,200 --> 01:13:27,640
- Oh God.
- I know. It was awful.

996
01:13:27,680 --> 01:13:29,600
And Sammy
would never do it, right?

997
01:13:29,640 --> 01:13:31,360
He would rather
go without a present

998
01:13:31,400 --> 01:13:35,000
than actually get up in front
of all those people, let alone sing.

999
01:13:35,040 --> 01:13:36,480
